- Program displays one of the provided road map files, which includes a grid of roads, road blocks scattered throughout the map, and a start and end point.
- User runs program from command line with 'Solve [map] [delay]' in which 'map' is the .txt file containing the particular map. The program will search for an un-blocked path from the start to end point using depth-first-search. It will display this path, step by step, in which 'delay' is the time taken betweeneach step being drawn. For example, 'Solve map1.txt 1000' will search for an un-blocked path on map1, and incrementally display a step of the path every second.